            "answer_text": "On Kindle you can\u2019t view the page number as you could change the font size and spacing of the ebook you\u2019re reading. However, you could view the reading progress on Kindle. That is you can view the pages read or the percentage of a book you\u2019re reading on your Kindle. The feature is called Time to Read. To use Time to Read, tap on the top of the screen and select Display Settings (Aa) icon, and then select the Reading Progress tab. You could choose from the following tracking options to be displayed at the bottom of the screen: Location in bookPage in book (if available)Time left in chapterTime left in bookNone",
