            },
            "answer_text": "Amazon has given the publishers an option to include page numbers from a particular paper edition with their Kindle e-book. Of course, they don\u2019t correspond to Kindle screens - you might read page 34 over three Kindle screens, or just one (if you select small type and narrow margins). If the book has paper-equivalent page numbers, the fact is noted on the product page like this:  To select page numbers for display, either keep tapping in the lower left corner of the page, or activate the menu, go to \u201cAa\u201d option, select \u201cReading progress\u201d (or something like that) tab and select from there. ",
